swingtree.style

Class StyleTrait<C extends javax.swing.JComponent>

  • java.lang.Object
    • swingtree.style.StyleTrait<C>
  • Type Parameters:
    C - The type of JComponent this StyleTrait is for.

    public final class StyleTrait<C extends javax.swing.JComponent>
extends java.lang.Object
    A StyleTrait is a set of properties that will be used to target specific JComponents matching said properties, so that you can apply custom Stylea to them.
    Instances of this are supposed to be created and registered inside custom StyleSheet extensions which you can use to apply custom styles to your UIs.
